        "client_msg_id": "154fee42-5ac7-4dd5-8b1f-d2d518646ba0",
        "type": "message",
        "text": "conversational UX is inherently 1D so generally less efficient if the search space is small and the classification scheme relatively obvious to the audience.\nAdditionally, when done via voice/response, it's inherently public, which is usually a detriment rather than a feature.\nLastly, people generally expect a conversational reply in a shorter time than other UI feedback, so it feels slower even if it isn't.",
